  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n\n3. Key Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Implementing robust compliance programs\n- Imposing significant penalties for violations\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Central banks\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n5. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Record-keeping\n- Reporting large or suspicious transactions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.",
